  "text": "Samples were collected with a citobrush and placed in 1 mL of specimen transport medium (Qiagen, Gaithersburg, MD), sent to the Retroviruses and Papillomavirus Unit of the National Center for Microbiology in Madrid, and stored at −20°C until required for testing. Anal HR-HPV infection was genotyped using polymerase chain reaction (PCR) amplification, followed by reverse line blot hybridization, using the Linear Array HPV [CITATION_1] .",
